# Frontend Patterns

## Stack
- Blade templates for HTML
- Alpine.js for interactivity (expand/collapse, loading states, form handling)
- Tailwind CSS 4 for styling — utility classes only, no custom CSS files

## Layout
All pages extend `layouts/app.blade.php`:
```blade
@extends('layouts.app')

@section('title', 'Page Title')

@section('content')
    <!-- Page content -->
@endsection
```

## Alpine.js Usage
Use `x-data`, `x-show`, `x-on` for interactive elements:
```blade
<div x-data="{ expanded: false }">
    <button x-on:click="expanded = !expanded">Toggle</button>
    <div x-show="expanded" x-transition>
        <!-- Expandable content -->
    </div>
</div>
```

## Design Principles
- Clean, professional, minimal — not flashy
- Score badge: circular, color-coded (green 80+, yellow 50-79, red <50)
- Check results: clear pass/warn/fail icons with expandable details
- Mobile responsive
- Accessible: proper labels, contrast ratios, semantic HTML
